StanfordCPPLib — Licensing status (UNRESOLVED)
==============================================

**WARNING — This vendored copy lacks a clear upstream LICENSE file.**

This directory contains code from the Stanford C++ Library, originally
developed by Eric Roberts and contributors at Stanford University for the
CS106B / CS106X introductory programming courses. The upstream historical
distribution carried different licence statements at different points in
time (notably a permissive licence in the 2014-era release shipped with
the textbook "Programming Abstractions in C++").

The Mailspring/ActunaMail vendored copy in this directory **does not
contain an upstream LICENSE file**, and the in-source comments do not
declare a licence.

Risk classification (per `analysis/24-license-compliance-audit.md`
§9 Strefa G.3): **⚠️ unresolved — investigate before commercial
distribution.**

Mitigation options for ActunaMail:

  1. Locate and incorporate the original Stanford CS106B distribution's
     licence file (the historical permissive 2014 release), copy it here.
  2. Contact the original maintainers for clarification.
  3. Replace use of StanfordCPPLib in mailsync with an alternative
     (e.g. standard C++ exceptions / error reporting in lieu of
     `ErrorException`).

Until one of the above is completed, the BETA distribution of ActunaMail
relies on the academic/educational nature of the original library and
on Mailspring/Foundry376's prior vendoring of the same copy. This is
**not** a guarantee of clear commercial-distribution rights.

Tracking ticket: `backlog/75-license-mailsync-vendor-LICENSE-files.md`.
